Vol / Page: 63
Edition:
Quote: Inaka - the minnow. Its child is the mata (whitebait). The word `mata' is seldom used in the lists, the word inaka covering both parent and child.
Notes: c1880 South Island Maori Lists `Wahi Mahika Kai' in 1945 Beattie Maori Place-names of Canterbury

